msgid "The Text Encoding Initiative Guidelines for Electronic Text Encoding and Interchange (referred to as the <_:title-1/>) were first published in 1994 and represent a tremendous achievement in electronic text standards by providing a highly sophisticated structure for encoding electronic text. Digital librarians have benefited greatly from the standardization provided by these guidelines, and the potential for interoperability and long-term preservation of digital collections facilitated by their wide adoption."
